        "title": "5. `fetchers.py` — largest gap by far (~1000 lines, 18 ATS integrations, zero tests)",
        "content": "\nThe module docstring explicitly says the client is \"injectable so parsing logic is unit-testable against mocked transports\" — that design intent is currently unused.\n\n**Priority A — shared retry/parsing infra used by everything:**\n\n```python\n",
